        <poem_themes></poem_themes>
    </metadata>
    
    <body>
        <stanza> 
            <line>A little Bread -- a crust -- a crumb --</line> 
            <line>A little trust -- a demijohn --</line> 
            <line>Can keep the soul alive --</line> 
            <line>Not portly, mind! but breathing -- warm --</line> 
            <line>Conscious -- as old Napoleon,</line> 
            <line>The night before the Crown!</line> 
        </stanza>
        <stanza>
            <line>A modest lot -- A fame petite --</line> 
            <line>A brief Campaign of sting and sweet</line> 
            <line>Is plenty! Is enough!</line> 
            <line>A Sailor's business is the shore</line> 
            <line>A Soldier's -- balls! Who asketh more,</line> 
            <line>Must seek the neighboring life!</line> 
        </stanza>
    </body>
</poem>

<!--POST PLAIN TEXT OF POEM BELOW 

A little Bread - a crust - a crumb - 
A little trust - a demijohn - 
Can keep the soul alive - 
Not portly, mind! but breathing - warm - 
Conscious - as old Napoleon, 
The night before the Crown! 

A modest lot - A fame petite - 
A brief Campaign of sting and sweet 
Is plenty! Is enough! 
A Sailor's business is the shore 
A Soldier's - balls! Who asketh more, 
Must seek the neighboring life! 


